    <string name="settings_audio_sco_downsample">Downsample to 16 kHz</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_sco_downsample_desc">SCO call-channel bandwidth is limited. Downsampling improves compatibility but reduces quality.</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_volume_title">Volume normalization</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_volume_body">Automatically adjusts playback gain from embedded loudness metadata (ReplayGain), making songs with different mastering loudness sound more consistent.
 Based on the ITU-R BS.1770 loudness normalization standard.</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_gapless_title">Gapless playback</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_gapless_body">When the current song ends, switch directly to the next song decoder stream to remove the short silent gap commonly heard between tracks.

Useful for live albums, DJ mixes, and other continuous playback.</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_crossfade_title">Crossfade</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_crossfade_body">Starts the next song before the current one ends and overlaps both audio streams. A constant-power curve keeps the transition natural.

The overlap can be set from 1 to 12 seconds; 0 means off.</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_sco_title">SCO downsample</string>
    <string name="settings_audio_info_sco_body">Bluetooth SCO (Synchronous Connection Oriented) call-channel bandwidth is limited and usually supports only 8 kHz or 16 kHz.

When enabled, audio is resampled to 16 kHz before output. This improves compatibility with car devices but noticeably reduces quality, similar to a phone call.

When disabled, the system tries to output at the original sample rate; some devices may fail to play correctly.</string>
